Definition.WordDefinition: Previously \Pre"vi*ous*ly\, adv. Beforehand; antecedently; as, a plan previously formed. [1913 Webster]

previously adv : at an earlier time or formerly; "she had previously lived in Chicago"; "he was previously president of a bank"; "better than anything previously proposed"; "a previously unquestioned attitude"; "antecedently arranged" [syn: {antecedently}]
